DXVK per-application configuration overlays.

Each *.conf file here is copied by /usr/lib/ai-arch/pe-launch-wrapper.sh to
<exe_dir>/<basename>.dxvk.conf on game launch if the destination dir is
writable, otherwise passed via DXVK_CONFIG_FILE env.

Format: standard DXVK conf syntax — see upstream dxvk documentation at
https://github.com/doitsujin/dxvk/blob/master/dxvk.conf

File name MUST match the exe basename WITHOUT the .exe suffix, e.g.:
    witcher3.conf   -> matches witcher3.exe
    GTAV.conf       -> matches GTAV.exe (case-sensitive)

The wrapper also checks the lowercased basename, so witcher3.conf will
match Witcher3.EXE on case-insensitive filesystems.
